The 35-year-old taxi driver failed to stop at the scene. This prompted a police search, but the taxi driver handed himself into Preston Police Station just after 7am on Monday morning and is assisting officers with their investigation.

Police hope that footage from the car's cameras will help them work out the chain of events that led up to the man's injuries. The injured man is now in the Royal Melbourne Hospital.

